title: Matador Cup scores: New South Wales Blues beat Tasmanian Tigers thanks to Mitchell Starc and Nic Maddinson
text:
THE New South Wales Blues have maintained their perfect start to the Matador Cup season, beating the Tasmanian Tigers by eight wickets and 25 balls.
NSW’s victory was built off the back of a fine century from Nic Maddinson and yet another five-wicket haul from Mitchell Starc.
Having bowled Tasmania out for 217, rain delays meant the Blues were set a revised target of 193 from 43 overs.
Maddinson (118 not out) and Cowan (47) put on a 117-run opening stand before Tigers spinner Xavier Doherty threw a spanner into the works for NSW. The tweaker bowled Cowan in the 25th over and then had Steve Smith stumped on the very next delivery for a golden duck.
After starting the season with scores of 143 not out against the Cricket Australia XI and 72 against South Australia, Smith has failed to trouble the scorers in his last two games.
But with Maddinson in fine touch the result never looked in doubt for NSW. The 23-year-old raised his century off just 104 deliveries and then hit a huge six off Evan Gulbis to seal victory in the 38th over. Mitchell Starc tore through Tasmania’s batting order. Source: News Corp Australia
Earlier in the day Starc wreaked havoc with the ball, finishing with figures of 5-39 to bowl the Tigers out for 217.
In fairness to the Tigers, they did make Starc work for it. It wasn’t until the 19th over that the world’s best white-ball bowler opened his account, knocking over Dom Michael for 54.
Before that Gurinder Sandhu had accounted for Tim Paine (5) and Nathan Lyon had dismissed Ben Dunk for 23.
Impressive knocks from George Bailey (48) and James Faulkner (51) ensured the Tigers passed 200, but when the latter fell to Starc, the big left-hander clicked into gear, taking four wickets in nine deliveries.
Elsewhere, Victoria beat Western Australia thanks to a big performance from Glenn Maxwell.
Originally published as Starc and Maddinson tame Tigers
